h3 How Your Data is Used

h4 Privacy.

p Coposition is built on a foundation of user privacy. The following policy sets out how we use information relating to you and applies to all use of data by Coposition.

p We process data in accordance with the Data Protection Act 1998.  We will only send you marketing communications with your consent. By registering an account, you allow us to send you an initial email with instructions and tips, newsletters with Coposition news and updates, and follow up emails which alert you to actions required in connection to the authorisation of external apps to access your geolocation data. These emails can be turned off.

p We use information about you, including information derived from cookies and other tracking technologies, to help us operate our app and for marketing purposes.  We may disclose information about you in certain circumstances and this privacy policy may change from time to time.

p For the purpose of the Data Protection Act 1998, the data controller is Earlymarket Limited. If you have any concerns about your privacy please contact us using contact information available at https://coposition.com/help

h4 About Coposition.

p Coposition is a storage centre for your geolocation data, from which you can permit 3rd party applications to access your data and customise this flow of data. This geolocation data is created by the Coposition mobile app, which can be installed on numerous devices. 

p What data do we collect and how is it used?

p We may ask you for, or you may submit, personal and non-personal information and data to us when you use the App and the Coposition website. We use this data to register and administer your user account. We record your password in an encrypted format.
p We use your email address to contact you about your use of the Coposition services, to provide you with news about us and to offer you additional services. We also use your email address to synchronise your information across your user accounts and devices.
p We use your location data so that the map knows where you are.
p We may anonymise information about you and then aggregate it with information about other users in order to gain insights into how individuals are using Coposition services.
p When you get in contact with us we may keep records of what is communicated. This is to ensure we have a record of our discussion for future reference and so we can provide services to you more efficiently.
p We might collect sensitive information about you, but we will never collect your sensitive information without your explicit consent.

h4 Location data.

p The Coposition mobile app, and website, can be used to create location data. This location data is sent to our secure servers, and stored as your data. You can create, edit, and destroy your location data as you please through the Coposition platform, and doing this updates the master copy of this data. Your location data can be shared with other users and with 3rd party applications, once you as the owner of the data have authorised this access to your data. How this data can be accessed, and the accuracy of this data, is at the discretion of the user, subject to the available options provided by Coposition. You can update your access permissions and the manner in which your location data is created, including frequency of check-in creation, through the Coposition mobile app and the Coposition website. If auto-checkin is turned on, your location may be sent to the Coposition servers automatically. Users can make their data publicly visible, and if so any viewer of the public sharing URL can view user location data. 

h4 Cookies and app usage analysis.

p We use 'cookiesâ€™ and similar technologies on the mobile app and website ("Cookies"). Cookies are small computer files which Coposition may store in your Internet browser, enabling your Internet browser and Coposition to communicate with each other. Other similar technologies may operate in a different way but, like Cookies, are used to analyse how Coposition services are being used.
p Cookies enable us to record anonymous information about you, including: the type of Internet browser you use to access Coposition services, your computer operating system, the websites you visited before accessing Coposition services, the areas of the Coposition website you visit, how long you visit Coposition websites and your IP address (which can provide information about your approximate geographic location). We do not use Cookies to determine your individual identity.

